newsitem.title: DUBAI: Stocks on Oman's market end the week higher.
newsitem.headline: Stocks on Oman's market end the week higher.

text.p: Shares on Oman's stock exchange moved higher in the week to Wednesday in trade dominated by banking and investment sector stocks, the bourse said.
The Muscat Securities Market said the index closed at 187.33 points from 186.06 last week.
Some 187,000 shares in Oman International Bank shares worth 474,000 rials were traded in the week, but the share closed unchanged at 2.580 rials.
Oman National Holding Co continued its climb, with 87,000 shares worth 359,000 rials changing hands. It closed at 4.110 rials from 4.080 rials last week.
